elements.title: New York Biltmore Hotel
elements.contents: ... that the kissing room of the New York Biltmore Hotel (pictured) remained after the rest of the hotel had been demolished?

elements.title: Angela Merkel
elements.contents: ... that former German chancellor Angela Merkel's grandfather likely fought against Germany in World War I?

elements.title: a TV station
elements.contents: ... that a division of the Buffalo Sabres ice hockey team lost $6 million in less than three years running a TV station?

elements.title: Jug Bennett
elements.contents: ... that Jug Bennett, Merle Zuver, Lyle Sturgeon, Wuert Engelmann, Zud Schammel, Hal Hinte and Frank Butler all played for Green Bay Packers Hall of Fame head coach Curly Lambeau during the 1930s and 1940s?

elements.title: Battle of the Indus
elements.contents: ... that when Jalal al-Din realised that he would be defeated at the Battle of the Indus, he rode his horse off a 30-foot (10 m) cliff into the Indus River?

elements.title: Herbert Jackson
elements.contents: ... that the unusual trousers worn by crammer Herbert Jackson led to rumours among students of the University of Oxford that they concealed a coiled-up tail?

elements.title: Libellus de vocabulis rei militaris
elements.contents: ... that the Libellus de vocabulis rei militaris has been misattributed to Cicero, Cato, Pomponius Laetus and a mysterious Modestus?

elements.title: Chip Hawkes
elements.contents: ... that Chip Hawkes got his nickname after turning up at gigs while covered in wood shavings?
